{"id":14881750,"mediaExerciseId":"9e700ce0-c2ee-4593-b1a2-4b3891f1f8d5","exerciseName":"1","chapterName":"21","chapterTitle":"International Corporate Finance","groupId":null,"groupTitle":null,"isPremium":true,"sectionName":"21.1","sectionTitle":"Terminology","pageNumber":713,"solutions":[{"id":5960815,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we are asked to determine the difference of Eurobond and a foreign bond and define Eurodollars.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"## 1a.\n\nWe are asked to determine the difference of Eurobond and a foreign bond.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":66,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/57b44959d52914d591987cebc5147515/3ef32178fffa613729f2984d97182818/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/57b44959d52914d591987cebc5147515/3ef32178fffa613729f2984d97182818/lateximg.png","width":497}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"**Eurobond** is denominated in a *single currency* even though it is a bond that has been *issued  to multiple countries*. Usually, it is denominated in the issuer's currency.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":105,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/57b44959d52914d591987cebc5147515/721a2752f0256a5ebe6ab45a106e2945/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/57b44959d52914d591987cebc5147515/721a2752f0256a5ebe6ab45a106e2945/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"On the other hand, a **foreign bond** is a bond that is *issued in a single country*. It is usually denominated in that country's currency.\n\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":68,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/57b44959d52914d591987cebc5147515/3b8ddaa5f80a92c90557097080b707f5/lateximg_large.png","width":995},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/57b44959d52914d591987cebc5147515/3b8ddaa5f80a92c90557097080b707f5/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"Therefore, the difference of Eurobond is that it is issued in **multiple countries but denominated in the issuer's currency** while the foreign bond is issued in a **single country and denominated in that country's currency**. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":105,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/57b44959d52914d591987cebc5147515/9269312e83397a7a0da5629db317824f/lateximg_large.png","width":995},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/57b44959d52914d591987cebc5147515/9269312e83397a7a0da5629db317824f/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"## 1b.\n\nWe are asked to define Eurodollars","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":28,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/57b44959d52914d591987cebc5147515/d5b31ba6c5f850194308a61218cf3666/lateximg_large.png","width":837},"regular":{"height":15,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/29/57b44959d52914d591987cebc5147515/d5b31ba6c5f850194308a61218cf3666/lateximg.png","width":417}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6},{"columns":[{"text":"Recall that a **Eurobond** is denominated in a *single currency* even though it is a bond that has been *issued  to multiple countries*. Usually, it is denominated in the issuer's currency.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":7},{"columns":[{"text":"Therefore, a **Eurodollar** is a bond issued to multiple countries that is denominated in *dollars*.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":8},{"columns":[{"text":"As a conclusion, we differentiate Eurobond and a foreign bond. We have also defined a Eurodollar.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":9}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"d977d742-6a4f-409b-99a9-2cfe65590e5c","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":9}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881751,"exerciseName":"1","page":714,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"a1ddd26f-cca3-426e-99ba-e6b8567ad000","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-21-exercises-1-a1ddd26f-cca3-426e-99ba-e6b8567ad000"},{"id":14881752,"exerciseName":"2","page":714,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"060136d6-edf1-4b06-aa29-44ff7f3a546e","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-21-exercises-2-060136d6-edf1-4b06-aa29-44ff7f3a546e"}],"previousExercises":[{"id